transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, how can I help you today?

Speaker 2: How are you doing, sir?

Speaker 1: Doing well, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Thank you for taking my call.

Speaker 1: The reason for my call is I called about two weeks ago and talked to one of your associates.

Speaker 2: I received your product, and I've tried it on three different occasions with absolutely no results.

Speaker 1: And he mentioned that I didn't see anything to call back for a refund, so that's why I'm calling.

Speaker 2: Sure.

Speaker 1: What's your zip code and your last name to pull up your account here in our system?

Speaker 2: Zip code 60143.

Speaker 1: My last name is Manna, M-A-N-N-A, Mark.

Speaker 2: Okay, I pulled you up here.

Speaker 1: All right, so we're just going to go ahead and email you the return instructions, sir.

Speaker 2: That way you can send the remaining pills back for the refund.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: You'll receive them in your email inbox in a few moments.

Speaker 1: However, I went ahead and stopped any future order for you, so you're all set today.

Speaker 2: Okay, so just follow the instructions, and that's it?

Speaker 1: Yeah, exactly.

Speaker 2: Just follow the instructions in the email, send it back for the refund, and once it gets to our pharmacy, you'll be able to obtain that.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you.

Speaker 2: No problem.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
